isoiec80000:term-t6-16-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "electric susceptibility"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t6-16-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "chi"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t6-16 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "6-16" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t6-16-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t6-16-0 ;
  skos:definition """for linear media, scalar quantity expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
bb(ii(P)) = epsilon_0 chi bb(ii(E))
++++

where stem:[bb(ii(P))] is electric polarization (<<t6-7>>), stem:[epsilon_0] is the electric constant (<<t6-14.1>>), and stem:[bb(ii(E))] is electric field strength (<<t6-10>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """stem:[chi = epsilon_r - 1] where stem:[epsilon_r] is relative permittivity (<<t6-15>>)

Electric susceptibility stem:[chi] is a property of a medium. For an inhomogeneous medium, electric susceptibility stem:[chi] depends on position.

For an isotropic medium, stem:[chi] is a scalar quantity; for an anisotropic medium, stem:[chi] is a second order tensor.

See <<iec60050-121,locality:item=\"121-12-19\">>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-6 .